#### Subdisciplines

The main branches are defined by material class: ceramics, metals, polymers, and composites. Then there are the overarching, material-independent areas: [characterization](/Characterization_(materials_science)), [computational materials science](/Computational_materials_science), and [materials informatics](/Materials_informatics). Specific focuses include [crystallography](/Crystallography), [surface science](/Surface_science), [tribology](/Tribology), and [microelectronics](/Microelectronics).

